        <num>Chapter 59-2</num>
        <heading>Property Tax Act</heading>
        <section eId="sec_59_2_1207">
          <num>59-2-1207</num>
          <heading>Renumbered 1/1/2026</heading>
          <content>
            <p>Renumbered 1/1/2026
59-2-1207.
Claim applied against tax liability -- One claimant per household per year.
(1)
A county shall apply as provided in Subsection
59-2-1206(1)(c)
the amount of a credit under this part against:
(a)
a claimant's property tax liability; or
(b)
the property tax liability of a spouse who was a member of the claimant's household in the year in which the claimant applies for a homeowner's credit under this part.
(2)
Only one claimant per household per year is entitled to payment under this part.
Amended by Chapter
221
, 2001 General Session
Amended by Chapter
310
, 2001 General Session</p>
          </content>
          <subsection eId="59_2_1207__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>A county shall apply as provided in Subsection the amount of a credit under this part against:</p>
            </content>
            <paragraph eId="59_2_1207__subsec_1__para_a">
              <num>(a)</num>
              <content>
                <p>a claimant's property tax liability; or</p>
              </content>
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph eId="59_2_1207__subsec_1__para_b">
              <num>(b)</num>
              <content>
                <p>the property tax liability of a spouse who was a member of the claimant's household in the year in which the claimant applies for a homeowner's credit under this part.</p>
              </content>
            </paragraph>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="59_2_1207__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Only one claimant per household per year is entitled to payment under this part.</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
        </section>
